{"type":"message","id":"64d10b49","parentId":"d5f2b1b9","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:28:57.240Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[[reply_to_current]] 现在这个状态很像：**设备端已经打到 gateway 了，但这边还没出现待审批请求**。  \n我刚查了两次，当前 `pending` 还是空的，所以现在直接跑 `openclaw devices approve` 也批不到东西。\n\n你现在按这个顺序来最稳：\n\n1. 在新设备上**重新发起一次连接 / 重新扫码**\n2. 看到 `pairing required` 后，**不要退出那个页面**\n3. 立刻在服务端执行：\n   ```bash\n   openclaw devices list\n   ```\n   或者如果你那边 CLI 支持：\n   ```bash\n   openclaw devices approve --latest\n   ```\n\n如果还是一直不出现 pending，那问题就不是“没批准”，而是**请求没真正登记到 pairing 队列**。那时要查的就是：\n- 你现在是**扫码配对**还是**手填地址**\n- gateway 暴露的是不是正确地址\n- bootstrap/setup code 有没有过期\n\n你现在最好直接把这两样贴我：\n```bash\nopenclaw devices list\nopenclaw qr --json\n```\n我可以直接帮你判断卡在哪一层。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":263,"output":272,"cacheRead":43904,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44439,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1773851324969}}
{"type":"message","id":"3b57e4e0","parentId":"64d10b49","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:51:14.409Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-19 00:51:13 GMT+8] Feishu[default] DM | ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3 [msg:om_x100b5499ced8dca4b35c3958e3440d7]\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"om_x100b5499ced8dca4b35c3958e3440d7\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"sender\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Thu 2026-03-19 00:51 GMT+8\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"id\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\",\n  \"name\": \"ou_664eb5978d7a2e16127187d1c18827d3\"\n}\n```\n\ncurl -sSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/okx/onchainos-skills/main/install.sh | sh"}],"timestamp":1773852674406}}
{"type":"message","id":"1b7628c1","parentId":"3b57e4e0","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:51:25.174Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"这条命令是直接从 GitHub 拉脚本然后执行，先别急着跑，我先帮你做下安全审查。"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_wblTOaHS8n3Ti2oRYTZDA7Fb","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/home/zbb/.openclaw/skills/skill-vetter/SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":42079,"output":292,"cacheRead":2560,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":44931,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773852674408}}
{"type":"message","id":"18337229","parentId":"1b7628c1","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:51:25.186Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_wblTOaHS8n3Ti2oRYTZDA7Fb","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\nname: skill-vetter\nversion: 1.0.0\ndescription: Security-first skill vetting for AI agents. Use before installing any skill from ClawdHub, GitHub, or other sources. Checks for red flags, permission scope, and suspicious patterns.\n---\n\n# Skill Vetter 🔒\n\nSecurity-first vetting protocol for AI agent skills. **Never install a skill without vetting it first.**\n\n## When to Use\n\n- Before installing any skill from ClawdHub\n- Before running skills from GitHub repos\n- When evaluating skills shared by other agents\n- Anytime you're asked to install unknown code\n\n## Vetting Protocol\n\n### Step 1: Source Check\n\n```\nQuestions to answer:\n- [ ] Where did this skill come from?\n- [ ] Is the author known/reputable?\n- [ ] How many downloads/stars does it have?\n- [ ] When was it last updated?\n- [ ] Are there reviews from other agents?\n```\n\n### Step 2: Code Review (MANDATORY)\n\nRead ALL files in the skill. Check for these **RED FLAGS**:\n\n```\n🚨 REJECT IMMEDIATELY IF YOU SEE:\n─────────────────────────────────────────\n• curl/wget to unknown URLs\n• Sends data to external servers\n• Requests credentials/tokens/API keys\n• Reads ~/.ssh, ~/.aws, ~/.config without clear reason\n• Accesses MEMORY.md, USER.md, SOUL.md, IDENTITY.md\n• Uses base64 decode on anything\n• Uses eval() or exec() with external input\n• Modifies system files outside workspace\n• Installs packages without listing them\n• Network calls to IPs instead of domains\n• Obfuscated code (compressed, encoded, minified)\n• Requests elevated/sudo permissions\n• Accesses browser cookies/sessions\n• Touches credential files\n─────────────────────────────────────────\n```\n\n### Step 3: Permission Scope\n\n```\nEvaluate:\n- [ ] What files does it need to read?\n- [ ] What files does it need to write?\n- [ ] What commands does it run?\n- [ ] Does it need network access? To where?\n- [ ] Is the scope minimal for its stated purpose?\n```\n\n### Step 4: Risk Classification\n\n| Risk Level | Examples | Action |\n|------------|----------|--------|\n| 🟢 LOW | Notes, weather, formatting | Basic review, install OK |\n| 🟡 MEDIUM | File ops, browser, APIs | Full code review required |\n| 🔴 HIGH | Credentials, trading, system | Human approval required |\n| ⛔ EXTREME | Security configs, root access | Do NOT install |\n\n## Output Format\n\nAfter vetting, produce this report:\n\n```\nSKILL VETTING REPORT\n═══════════════════════════════════════\nSkill: [name]\nSource: [ClawdHub / GitHub / other]\nAuthor: [username]\nVersion: [version]\n───────────────────────────────────────\nMETRICS:\n• Downloads/Stars: [count]\n• Last Updated: [date]\n• Files Reviewed: [count]\n───────────────────────────────────────\nRED FLAGS: [None / List them]\n\nPERMISSIONS NEEDED:\n• Files: [list or \"None\"]\n• Network: [list or \"None\"]  \n• Commands: [list or \"None\"]\n───────────────────────────────────────\nRISK LEVEL: [🟢 LOW / 🟡 MEDIUM / 🔴 HIGH / ⛔ EXTREME]\n\nVERDICT: [✅ SAFE TO INSTALL / ⚠️ INSTALL WITH CAUTION / ❌ DO NOT INSTALL]\n\nNOTES: [Any observations]\n═══════════════════════════════════════\n```\n\n## Quick Vet Commands\n\nFor GitHub-hosted skills:\n```bash\n# Check repo stats\ncurl -s \"https://api.github.com/repos/OWNER/REPO\" | jq '{stars: .stargazers_count, forks: .forks_count, updated: .updated_at}'\n\n# List skill files\ncurl -s \"https://api.github.com/repos/OWNER/REPO/contents/skills/SKILL_NAME\" | jq '.[].name'\n\n# Fetch and review SKILL.md\ncurl -s \"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/OWNER/REPO/main/skills/SKILL_NAME/SKILL.md\"\n```\n\n## Trust Hierarchy\n\n1. **Official OpenClaw skills** → Lower scrutiny (still review)\n2. **High-star repos (1000+)** → Moderate scrutiny\n3. **Known authors** → Moderate scrutiny\n4. **New/unknown sources** → Maximum scrutiny\n5. **Skills requesting credentials** → Human approval always\n\n## Remember\n\n- No skill is worth compromising security\n- When in doubt, don't install\n- Ask your human for high-risk decisions\n- Document what you vet for future reference\n\n---\n\n*Paranoia is a feature.* 🔒🦀\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773852685182}}
{"type":"message","id":"8fbf9f23","parentId":"18337229","timestamp":"2026-03-18T16:51:38.001Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Evaluating installation commands**\n\nI need to respond to the user’s request about an installation command, but first, I should vet it carefully. I’m considering using web_fetch or web_search to gather necessary information rather than relying on memory. Analyzing the risks is crucial here. I could look into the install script and repository stats, but the skill review indicates I should read all files. Since I only have the install script, I’ll fetch it safely without running any commands directly.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_Y6rRcnK3aa6ryDX2ny1251OO","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://raw.githubusercontent.com/okx/onchainos-skills/main/install.sh","extractMode":"text","maxChars":12000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":1188,"output":408,"cacheRead":44544,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":46140,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773852685187}}
